$$\forall P. \exists Y. (P Y) \supset (P a)$$

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

$$\Pi_{oo(o\iota)} (\lambda P_{o\iota}. \Sigma_{oo\iota} (\lambda Y_\iota. \supset_{ooo} (P Y) (P a)))$$

```elixir
pi = mk_pi_const.(type_io_o) |> mk_term()
p = mk_free_var("P", type_io)
sigma = mk_sigma_const.(type_io) |> mk_term()
y = mk_free_var("Y", type_i)
a = mk_const("a", type_i)
p_y = mk_appl_term(mk_term(p), mk_term(y))
p_a = mk_appl_term(mk_term(p), mk_term(a))

implication = implies_term |> mk_appl_term(p_y) |> mk_appl_term(p_a)
inner_abstr = implication |> mk_abstr_term(y)
exist = sigma |> mk_appl_term(inner_abstr)
outer_abstr = exist |> mk_abstr_term(p)

formula = mk_appl_term(pi, outer_abstr)
PrettyPrint.pp_term(formula)
```

```elixir
Tableaux.prove formula
```

$$\forall F. \forall X. (FX) = (F X)$$

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

$$\Pi_{oo(\iota\iota)}(\lambda F_{\iota\iota}. \Pi_{oo\iota}(\lambda X_\iota. =_{o\iota\iota} (F X) (F X)))$$

```elixir
f = mk_free_var("f", type_ii)
x = mk_free_var("x", type_i)
f_term = mk_term(f)
x_term = mk_term(x)
eq_term = mk_term(mk_equals_const.(type_i))
pi_io_term = mk_pi_const.(type_io) |> mk_term()
pi_ii_o_term = mk_pi_const.(type_ii_o) |> mk_term()

f_x = mk_appl_term(f_term, x_term)
equality = mk_appl_term(mk_appl_term(eq_term, f_x), f_x)
x_abstr = mk_abstr_term(equality, x)
f_abstr = mk_abstr_term(mk_appl_term(pi_io_term, x_abstr), f)

formula = mk_appl_term(pi_ii_o_term, f_abstr)
PrettyPrint.pp_term(formula)
```

```elixir
Tableaux.prove formula
```

## Functional Extensionality -> not provable

$$\forall f g. (\forall x. f(x) = g(x)) \supset f = g$$

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

$$\Pi_{oo(\iota\iota)} (\lambda F_{\iota\iota}. \Pi_{oo(\iota\iota)} (\lambda G_{\iota\iota}. \supset_{ooo} (\Pi_{oo\iota} (\lambda X_\iota. =_{o\iota\iota} (F X) (G X))) ~ (=_{o(\iota\iota)(\iota\iota)} F G)))$$

```elixir
outer_pi = mk_pi_const.(type_ii_o) |> mk_term()
inner_pi = mk_pi_const.(type_io) |> mk_term()
left_eq = mk_equals_const.(type_i) |> mk_term()
right_eq = mk_equals_const.(type_ii) |> mk_term

f = mk_free_var("F", type_ii)
f_term = f |> mk_term()
g = mk_free_var("G", type_ii)
g_term = g |> mk_term()
x = mk_free_var("X", type_i)
x_term = x |> mk_term()

f_x = f_term |> mk_appl_term(x_term)
g_x = g_term |> mk_appl_term(x_term)

left_abstr = left_eq |> mk_appl_term(f_x) |> mk_appl_term(g_x) |> mk_abstr_term(x)
left_side = inner_pi |> mk_appl_term(left_abstr)
right_side = right_eq |> mk_appl_term(f_term) |> mk_appl_term(g_term)
implication = implies_term |> mk_appl_term(left_side) |> mk_appl_term(right_side)
g_abstr = implication |> mk_abstr_term(g)
g_quant = outer_pi |> mk_appl_term(g_abstr)
f_abstr = g_quant |> mk_abstr_term(f)

formula = outer_pi |> mk_appl_term(f_abstr)
PrettyPrint.pp_term formula
```

```elixir
TPTPParser.term_to_tptp(formula) |> IO.puts()
```

```elixir
Tableaux.prove formula
```

## Notions of Leibnitz Equality

$$a \overset\supset= b \coloneqq \forall P. Pa \supset Pb$$

$$a \overset\subset= b \coloneqq \forall P. P b \supset P a$$

$$a \overset\equiv= b \coloneqq \forall P. P a \equiv P b$$

```elixir
# needed constants and variables
pi = mk_pi_const.(type_io_o) |> mk_term()
p = mk_free_var("P", type_io)
p_term = mk_term p
x = mk_free_var("X", type_i)
x_term = mk_term x
y = mk_free_var("Y", type_i)
y_term = mk_term x
p_x = mk_appl_term(p_term, x_term)
p_y = mk_appl_term(p_term, y_term)
```

$$(X \overset\equiv= Y) \equiv (X \overset\supset= Y)$$

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

$$\equiv_{ooo}(\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda P_{o\iota}. \equiv_{ooo} (P X) (P Y)))~(\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda P_{o\iota}. \supset_{ooo} (P X) (P Y)))$$

```elixir
left_equiv = equivalent_term |> mk_appl_term(p_x) |> mk_appl_term(p_y)
left_abstr = left_equiv |> mk_abstr_term(p)
left_side = pi |> mk_appl_term(left_abstr)

right_impl = implies_term |> mk_appl_term(p_x) |> mk_appl_term(p_y)
right_abstr = right_impl |> mk_abstr_term(p)
right_side = pi |> mk_appl_term(right_abstr)

formula = equivalent_term |> mk_appl_term(left_side) |> mk_appl_term(right_side)
PrettyPrint.pp_term(formula)
```

```elixir
Tableaux.prove formula
```

$$(X \overset\supset= Y) \equiv (X \overset\subset= Y)$$

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

$$\equiv_{ooo}(\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda P_{o\iota}. \supset_{ooo} (P X) (P Y)))~(\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda P_{o\iota}. \supset_{ooo} (P Y) (P X)))$$

```elixir
left_impl = implies_term |> mk_appl_term(p_x) |> mk_appl_term(p_y)
left_abstr = left_impl |> mk_abstr_term(p)
left_side = pi |> mk_appl_term(left_abstr)

right_impl = implies_term |> mk_appl_term(p_y) |> mk_appl_term(p_y)
right_abstr = right_impl |> mk_abstr_term(p)
right_side = pi |> mk_appl_term(right_abstr)

formula = equivalent_term |> mk_appl_term(left_side) |> mk_appl_term(right_side)
PrettyPrint.pp_term(formula)
```

```elixir
Tableaux.prove formula
```

$$(a \overset\supset= b) \equiv (a \overset\subset= b)$$

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

$$\equiv_{ooo}(\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda P_{o\iota}. \supset_{ooo} (P a) (P b)))~(\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda P_{o\iota}. \supset_{ooo} (P b) (P a)))$$

```elixir
a = mk_const("a", type_i) |> mk_term()
b = mk_const("b", type_i) |> mk_term()
p_a = p_term |> mk_appl_term(a)
p_b = p_term |> mk_appl_term(b)

left_impl = implies_term |> mk_appl_term(p_a) |> mk_appl_term(p_b)
left_abstr = left_impl |> mk_abstr_term(p)
left_side = pi |> mk_appl_term(left_abstr)

right_impl = implies_term |> mk_appl_term(p_b) |> mk_appl_term(p_a)
right_abstr = right_impl |> mk_abstr_term(p)
right_side = pi |> mk_appl_term(right_abstr)

formula = equivalent_term |> mk_appl_term(left_side) |> mk_appl_term(right_side)
PrettyPrint.pp_term(formula)
```

```elixir
Tableaux.prove formula
```

## Surjective Cantor Theorem - Provable but not Satisfiable by System

$$\neg \exists F. \forall Y. \exists X. (F X) = Y$$

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

$$\neg_{oo} (\Sigma_{oo(o\iota\iota)}(\lambda F_{o\iota\iota}.~\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda Y_{o\iota}.~\Sigma_{oo\iota}(\lambda X_{\iota}.~=_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)}(F_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota) Y_{o\iota}))))$$

```elixir
equals_io_const = mk_equals_const.(type_io)
sigma_iio_o_const = mk_sigma_const.(type_iio_o)
pi_io_o_const = mk_pi_const.(type_io_o)
sigma_io_const = mk_sigma_const.(type_io)

equals_io_term = mk_term(equals_io_const)
sigma_iio_o_term = mk_term(sigma_iio_o_const)
pi_io_o_term = mk_term(pi_io_o_const)
sigma_io_term = mk_term(sigma_io_const)

f_var = mk_free_var("F", type_iio)
y_var = mk_free_var("Y", type_io)
x_var = mk_free_var("X", type_i)

f_term = mk_term(f_var)
y_term = mk_term(y_var)
x_term = mk_term(x_var)
```

```elixir
f_x = mk_appl_term(f_term, x_term)
equality = equals_io_term |> mk_appl_term(f_x) |> mk_appl_term(y_term)
x_abstr = mk_abstr_term(equality, x_var)
inner_sigma = mk_appl_term(sigma_io_term, x_abstr)
y_abstr = mk_abstr_term(inner_sigma, y_var)
outer_pi = mk_appl_term(pi_io_o_term, y_abstr)
f_abstr = mk_abstr_term(outer_pi, f_var)
outer_sigma = mk_appl_term(sigma_iio_o_term, f_abstr)

surj_cantor = mk_appl_term(neg_term, outer_sigma)

PrettyPrint.pp_term(surj_cantor)
```

```elixir
surj_cantor |> term_to_tptp() |> IO.puts()
```

```elixir
Tableaux.sat surj_cantor
```

```elixir
Tableaux.prove surj_cantor
```

```elixir
neg_term |> mk_appl_term(surj_cantor) |> Tableaux.sat
```

```elixir
neg_term |> mk_appl_term(surj_cantor) |> Tableaux.prove
```

## Appendix A: Cantor - Example by Hand (Lecture 16.7.25)

__Notation:__

$\mathbf{sk}^\mu_{\alpha\bar t}(\bar{T})$: Skolem term, indexed by $\mu$ mapping list of types $\bar t$ to type $\alpha$

$\mathbf{X}^\mu_\alpha$: Free variable, indexed by $\mu$ of type $\alpha$

$\star$: Tableaux closed

$\sigma$: Substitution

__Tableaux__

0\. $\neg \exists F_{o\iota\iota}. \forall Y_{o\iota}. \exists X_\iota. F X = Y$

1\. $\neg\neg\Sigma(\lambda F. \forall Y. \exists X. F X = Y)$ $\quad$ (Tableaux initialization: negate formula)

2\. $\Sigma(\lambda F. \forall Y. \exists X. F X = Y)$ $\quad$ $\neg\neg (1)$

3\. $\Pi(\lambda Y. \exists X. \mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota\iota} X = Y)$ $\quad$ $\Sigma (2)$

4\. $\Sigma(\lambda X. \mathbf{sk}^1 X = \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota})$ $\quad$ $\Pi (3)$

5\. $(\mathbf{sk}^1(\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota(o\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1)) ) \mathbf{X}^1$ $\quad$ $\Sigma$ (4)

6\. $\Pi(\lambda Z_\iota. ((\mathbf{sk}^1(\mathbf{sk}^2 \mathbf{X}^1)) Z_\iota) = (\mathbf{X}^1 Z_\iota))$ $\quad$ Def. $= (5)$

7\. $((\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 \mathbf{X}^1)) \mathbf{X}^1_\iota) = (\mathbf{X}^1 \mathbf{X}_\iota^2)$ $\quad$ $\Pi (6)$

8\. $((\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 \mathbf{X}^1)) \mathbf{X}^2) \equiv (\mathbf{X}^1 \mathbf{X}^2)$ $\quad$ Def. $= (7)$

_Branch A:_

9\. $((\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 \mathbf{X}^1)) \mathbf{X}^2)$ $\quad$ $\equiv (8)$

10\. $(\mathbf{X}^1 \mathbf{X}^2)$ $\quad$ $\equiv (8)$

$\star$ (9, 10) since

$\mathbf{X}^1 \mathbf{X}^2 \stackrel{?}{=} \neg ((\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 \mathbf{X}^1)) \mathbf{X}^2)$

$\sigma = \{\mathbf{X}^1 \gets (\lambda X_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{sk}^1 X X)), \mathbf{X}^2 \gets (\mathbf{sk}^2 (\lambda X_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{sk}^1 X X)))\}$ (solved by unification)

_Branch B:_

11\. $\neg ((\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 \mathbf{X}^1)) \mathbf{X}^2)$ $\quad$ $\equiv (8)$

11'\. $\neg ((\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 (\lambda X. \neg \mathbf{sk}^1 X X))) \mathbf{sk}^2 (\lambda X_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{sk}^1 X X))))$ $\quad$ $\sigma (11)$

12\. $\neg (\mathbf{X}^1 \mathbf{X}^2)$ $\quad$ $\equiv$ (8)

12'\. $\neg (\neg ((\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 (\lambda X. \neg \mathbf{sk}^1 X X))) \mathbf{sk}^2 (\lambda X_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{sk}^1 X X)))))$ $\quad$ $\sigma (12)$

13\. $(\mathbf{sk}^1 (\mathbf{sk}^2 (\lambda X. \neg \mathbf{sk}^1 X X))) \mathbf{sk}^2 (\lambda X_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{sk}^1 X X))$ $\quad$ $\neg\neg (12')$

$\star$ (13, 11') with $\sigma = \varnothing$

```elixir
# unification step closing branch A
h1 = mk_free_var_term("H1", type_io)
h2 = mk_free_var_term("H2", type_i)
sk1 = mk_const_term("sk1", type_iio)
sk2 = mk_const_term("sk2", type_io_i)

h1_h2 = h1 |> mk_appl_term(h2)
sk2_h1 = sk2 |> mk_appl_term(h1)
sk1_sk2_h1 = sk1 |> mk_appl_term(sk2_h1)
skolem_term = sk1_sk2_h1 |> mk_appl_term(h2)
neg_skolem_term = neg_term |> mk_appl_term(skolem_term)

unify({h1_h2, neg_skolem_term}) |> PrettyPrint.pp_res
```

## Appendix B: Negation of Cantor's Surjective Theorem by Hand

```elixir
neg_term |> mk_appl_term(surj_cantor) |> Tableaux.prove
```

0\. $\Sigma_{oo(o\iota\iota)}(\lambda F_{o\iota\iota}.~\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda Y_{o\iota}.~\Sigma_{oo\iota}(\lambda X_{\iota}.~=_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)}(F_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota) Y_{o\iota})))$

1\. $\neg(\Sigma_{oo(o\iota\iota)}(\lambda F_{o\iota\iota}.~\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda Y_{o\iota}.~\Sigma_{oo\iota}(\lambda X_{\iota}.~=_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)}(F_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota) Y_{o\iota}))))$ $\quad$ Tableaux initialization

2\. $\neg(\Pi_{oo(o\iota)}(\lambda Y_{o\iota}.~\Sigma_{oo\iota}(\lambda X_{\iota}.~=_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)}(\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota) Y_{o\iota})))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Sigma (1)$

3\. $\neg(\Sigma_{oo\iota}(\lambda X_{\iota}.~=_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)}(\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota})))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Pi (2)$

4\. $\neg(=_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)}(\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota}))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Sigma (3)$

5\. $\neg(\Pi_{oo\iota}(\lambda X_{\iota}. =_{ooo} ((\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota) X_\iota) ~ ((\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota}) X_\iota)))$ $\quad$ $= (4)$

6\. $\neg(=_{ooo} ((\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota)) ~ ((\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota}) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota)))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Pi (5)$

7\. $\neg(\equiv ((\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{oo\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota)) ~ ((\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota}) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{oo\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota)))$ $\quad$ $\neg= (6)$

_Branch A:_

8\. $\neg((\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota))$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (7)$

9\. $(\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota}) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota)$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (7)$

No unification found

10\. $\neg(\Pi_{oo(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda Y_{o\iota}. \Sigma_{oo\iota} (\lambda X_\iota. =_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)} (\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota) Y_{o\iota})))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Sigma (1)$

11\. $\neg(\Sigma_{oo\iota} (\lambda X_\iota. =_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)} (\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^3_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota})))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Pi (10)$

12\. $\neg(=_{o(o\iota)(o\iota)} (\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^3_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota}))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Sigma (11)$

13\. $\neg(\Pi_{oo\iota} (\lambda X_\iota. =_{ooo} (\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota X_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^3_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota)))$ $\quad$ $\neg= (12)$

14\. $\neg(=_{ooo} (\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota (\mathbf{sk}^4_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota)) ~ (\mathbf{sk}^3_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} (\mathbf{sk}^4_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota)))$ $\quad$ $\neg\Pi (13)$

15\. $\neg(\equiv (\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota (\mathbf{sk}^4_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota)) ~ (\mathbf{sk}^3_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} (\mathbf{sk}^4_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota)))$ $\quad$ $\neg= (14)$

_Branch AA:_

16\. $\neg(\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota (\mathbf{sk}^4_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota))$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (15)$

$\star$ with $\sigma_{AA} = \{\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \gets (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota)))\}$

_Branch AB (including $\sigma_{AA}$):_

17\. $\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota (\mathbf{sk}^4_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^4_\iota)$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (15)$

$\star$ with $\sigma_{AB} = \sigma_{AA} \cup \{\mathbf{X}^3_{o\iota\iota} \gets (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^6_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))) \}$

_Branch B (including $\sigma_{AB}$):_

18\. $\neg(\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))) \mathbf{X}^2_\iota))$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (7)$

19\. $\neg((\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota)))) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))) \mathbf{X}^2_\iota))$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (7)$

```elixir
# attempted unification to close branch A
type_iio_io = mk_type(type_io, [type_iio])
type_iio_ii = mk_type(type_ii, [type_iio])

sk1 = mk_const_term("sk1", type_iio_io)
sk2 = mk_const_term("sk2", type_iio_ii)

x1 = mk_free_var_term("X1", type_iio)
x2 = mk_free_var_term("X2", type_i)

x1_x2 = mk_appl_term(x1, x2)
sk2_x1_x2 = sk2 |> mk_appl_term(x1) |> mk_appl_term(x2)
sk1_x1 = mk_appl_term(sk1, x1)

neg_line_8 = mk_appl_term(x1_x2, sk2_x1_x2)
line_9 = mk_appl_term(sk1_x1, sk2_x1_x2)

PrettyPrint.pp_term(neg_line_8) |> IO.puts()
PrettyPrint.pp_term(line_9) |> IO.puts()

unify({line_9, neg_line_8}) |> PrettyPrint.pp_res()
```

```elixir
sk3 = mk_const_term("sk3", type_iio_io)
sk4 = mk_const_term("sk4", type_iio_ii)

x3 = mk_free_var_term("X3", type_iio)
x4 = mk_free_var_term("X4", type_i)

x3_x4 = mk_appl_term(x3, x4)
sk4_x3_x4 = sk4 |> mk_appl_term(x3) |> mk_appl_term(x4)

line_16 = mk_appl_term(neg_term, mk_appl_term(x3_x4, sk4_x3_x4))

PrettyPrint.pp_term(line_16) |> IO.puts()

unify({line_16, neg_line_8}) |> PrettyPrint.pp_res()
```

$\neg((\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} \mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota))$

$\mathbf{X}^1_{o\iota\iota} \gets \lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))$

$\neg((\lambda X_\iota. \neg(\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota X_\iota)) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))) \mathbf{X}^2_\iota))$

$\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))) \mathbf{X}^2_\iota)$

```elixir
x5 = mk_free_var_term("X5", type_iio)
x = mk_free_var("X", type_i)
y = mk_free_var("Y", type_i)

x5_x_y = x5 |> mk_appl_term(mk_term(x)) |> mk_appl_term(mk_term(y))
new_x1 = mk_abstr_term(mk_abstr_term(mk_appl_term(neg_term, x5_x_y), y), x)

x5_x2 = mk_appl_term(x5, x2)
x5_x2_x = mk_appl_term(x5_x2, mk_term(x))

skolem_term = sk2 |> mk_appl_term(new_x1) |> mk_appl_term(x2)

new_line_8 = mk_appl_term(x5_x2, skolem_term)

PrettyPrint.pp_term(new_line_8) |> IO.puts()
```

```elixir
line_17 = mk_appl_term(x3_x4, sk4_x3_x4)
neg_new_line_8 = mk_appl_term(neg_term, new_line_8)

PrettyPrint.pp_term(line_17) |> IO.puts()
PrettyPrint.pp_term(neg_new_line_8) |> IO.puts()

unify({line_17, neg_new_line_8}) |> PrettyPrint.pp_res()
```

18\. $\neg(\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} \mathbf{X}^2_\iota (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))) \mathbf{X}^2_\iota))$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (7)$

19\. $\neg((\mathbf{sk}^1_{o\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota)))) (\mathbf{sk}^2_{\iota\iota(o\iota\iota)} (\lambda X_\iota. (\lambda Y_\iota. \neg (\mathbf{X}^5_{o\iota\iota} X_\iota Y_\iota))) \mathbf{X}^2_\iota))$ $\quad$ $\neg\equiv (7)$

```elixir
neg_line_18 = new_line_8

